# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LLM provider config for the agent-worker container (the dependency judge).
#   cd deploy && cp agent.env.example agent.env   # agent.env is gitignored
# Loaded by the `agent` service (env_file, optional). Without this file the
# judge uses the image defaults: provider=ollama against the HOST daemon via
# host.docker.internal:11434.
#
# Why a SEPARATE file (not deploy/.env): .env only feeds compose ${...}
# interpolation and never reaches containers by itself, while this file is
# injected wholesale into the agent container only — so the judge gets exactly
# its own vars and none of the stack secrets. See deploy/README.md.
#
# Pick ONE provider block. base_url note: openrouter/anthropic-api ignore it;
# for openai-api keep it EMPTY — set `NORN_AGENT_BASE_URL=` in deploy/.env so
# the compose default (host Ollama) does not leak into the OpenAI client.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- ollama on the host (default; no secret) --------------------------------
# NORN_AGENT_PROVIDER=ollama
# NORN_AGENT_MODEL=gemma4:e2b
# NORN_AGENT_OUTPUT_MODE=native

# --- OpenAI platform key -----------------------------------------------------
# NORN_AGENT_PROVIDER=openai-api
# NORN_AGENT_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# NORN_AGENT_OUTPUT_MODE=tool
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# --- OpenAI OAuth bearer (see docs/guide/agent/README.md for the flow) -------
# NORN_AGENT_PROVIDER=openai-oauth
# NORN_AGENT_MODEL=<model your plan allows>
# NORN_AGENT_OUTPUT_MODE=tool
# NORN_OPENAI_OAUTH_TOKEN=...

# --- OpenRouter (one key, many vendors; model = <vendor>/<model>) ------------
# NORN_AGENT_PROVIDER=openrouter
# NORN_AGENT_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5
# NORN_AGENT_OUTPUT_MODE=tool
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# --- Anthropic direct ---------------------------------------------------------
# NORN_AGENT_PROVIDER=anthropic-api
# NORN_AGENT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5
# NORN_AGENT_OUTPUT_MODE=tool
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
